Defendant Michael T. Smulders in court with attorney William Henry Gergen.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Victim rights compliance. Discussion held on PSI. ADA Sempf heard. Atty Gergen heard. Defendant makes statement. Court heard and imposes sentence:

3 years Initial Confinement;
3 Extended Supervision;
Consecutive to any other sentence(s) previously imposed;
Not eligible for Challenge Incarceration & Substance Abuse Programs;
15 days presentence credit;
No contact with anyone under 18 w/o consent of agent - w/exception of nieces/nephews/grandchildren w/supervision as approved by agent;
Computer/Internet/Social Networking Use all at discretion of agent;
AODA & follow through;
Sex Offender Assessment & follow through;
DNA sample & surcharge;
Random UAs;
Comply w/Sex Offender Registry;
Costs
